This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it deals with hypernymy discovery in text-rich heterogeneous information networks. It also involves the use of textual patterns and distributional representations, which are common techniques in NLP. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves the development of a new framework for hypernymy inference. Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) are also possible sub-categories as the paper deals with information networks and the use of context in modeling hypernymy.
